Document: PacketPeerUDP
Path: godot/classes/class_packetpeerudp.rst
Summary: Provides UDP network communication functionality.

PacketPeerUDP is a high-level UDP interface. It allows you to send and receive packets of data over the network using the User Datagram Protocol. UDP is a connectionless protocol, meaning it doesn't establish a persistent connection like TCP. This makes it faster but less reliable, as packets can be lost, duplicated, or arrive out of order. PacketPeerUDP handles some of this by providing methods to check for available data and to get the sender's address.

Inherits: PacketPeer < RefCounted

This class is the base for network communication using UDP. It provides methods for binding to a local port, connecting to a remote host, sending data, and receiving data. It also includes functionality to check for errors and the status of the connection.

Key Rule: UDP is connectionless and unreliable. Packet loss, duplication, and out-of-order delivery are possible. PacketPeerUDP provides tools to manage this, but application-level logic may be needed for robust communication.
