Document: PacketPeerUDP
Path: godot/classes/class_packetpeerudp.rst
Summary: Provides methods for sending and receiving UDP packets, including binding to ports, connecting to hosts, and managing multicast groups.

Method: bind(port: int, bind_address: String = "*", recv_buf_size: int = 65536) → Error
Binds this PacketPeerUDP to the specified port and bind_address with a buffer size, allowing it to receive incoming packets. If bind_address is "*", it binds to all available addresses. If it's "0.0.0.0" or "::", it binds to all addresses of that IP type. If it's a specific address, it binds only to that interface.

Method: close() → void
Closes the PacketPeerUDP's underlying UDP socket.

Method: connect_to_host(host: String, port: int) → Error
Connects this UDP peer to the given host/port pair. This means incoming packets from different addresses are discarded, and outgoing packets are always sent to the connected address. Future calls to set_dest_address are not allowed. This method does not send data; use put_var or put_packet for that. Note: Connecting does not protect against IP spoofing; consider encryption like TLS or DTLS for sensitive information.

Method: get_local_port() → int
Returns the local port to which this peer is bound.

Method: get_packet_ip() → String
Returns the IP of the remote peer that sent the last received packet.

Method: get_packet_port() → int
Returns the port of the remote peer that sent the last received packet.

Method: is_bound() → bool
Returns whether this PacketPeerUDP is bound to an address and can receive packets.

Method: is_socket_connected() → bool
Returns true if the UDP socket is open and has been connected to a remote address.

Method: join_multicast_group(multicast_address: String, interface_name: String) → Error
Joins the multicast group specified by multicast_address using the interface identified by interface_name. Multiple interfaces can join the same group. Note: Some Android devices may require the CHANGE_WIFI_MULTICAST_STATE permission for multicast to work.

Method: leave_multicast_group(multicast_address: String, interface_name: String) → Error
Removes the interface identified by interface_name from the multicast group specified by multicast_address.

Method: set_broadcast_enabled(enabled: bool) → void
Enables or disables sending of broadcast packets. This option is disabled by default. Note: Some Android devices may require the CHANGE_WIFI_MULTICAST_STATE permission and this option to be enabled to receive broadcast packets too.

Method: set_dest_address(host: String, port: int) → Error
Sets the destination address and port for sending packets and variables. A hostname will be resolved using DNS if needed. Note: set_broadcast_enabled must be enabled before sending packets to a broadcast address (e.g., 255.255.255.255).

Method: wait() → Error
Waits for a packet to arrive on the bound address. This method cannot be interrupted once called. A workaround involves sending a specific "death pill" packet to signal termination.

GDScript:
socket = PacketPeerUDP.new()
# Server
socket.set_dest_address("127.0.0.1", 789)
socket.put_packet("Time to stop".to_ascii_buffer())

# Client
while socket.wait() == OK:
    var data = socket.get_packet().get_string_from_ascii()
    if data == "Time to stop":
        return

C#:
var socket = new PacketPeerUdp();
// Server
socket.SetDestAddress("127.0.0.1", 789);
socket.PutPacket("Time to stop".ToAsciiBuffer());

// Client
while (socket.Wait() == OK)
{
    string data = socket.GetPacket().GetStringFromASCII();
    if (data == "Time to stop")
    {
        return;
    }
}